This script resizes and plays a gif file according to
the entered parameters.

Example

./giftile 10.gif X Y

Parameter 1: Gif file you want to use
parameter 2: Screen horizontal size dividing number
parameter 3: Screen vertical size dividing number

So if you want a window that is 1/4 of your screen you divide
both axes with 2. If you want a window that is one half of 
your screen you use X divider 2 and Y divider 1

Examples

./giftile 10.gif 2 1
 ________
|    ####|
|    ####|
 ''''''''

./giftile 10.gif 2 2
 ________
|    ####|
|        |
 ''''''''

./giftile 10.gif 4 2 
 ________
|      ##|
|        |
 ''''''''
./giftile 10.gif 4 1
 ________
|      ##|
|      ##|
 ''''''''

